Auth APIs — Auth APIs
1. 
Login
Method: POST
Endpoint: /auth/login
Description: Authenticates a user and returns an access token.

2. 
Logout
Method: POST
Endpoint: /auth/logout
Description: Logs out the currently authenticated user and invalidates the session.

3. 
Refresh
Method: GET
Endpoint: /auth/refresh
Description: Refreshes the authentication token for an active session.

Resource APIs — Resource APIs

1.
Get order
Method: GET
Endpoint: /orders
Description: Retrieves a list of all orders.

2. 
Post order
Method: POST
Endpoint: /orders
Description: Creates a new order.
Request Body (JSON):
{    "item": "RAM",    "quantity": 3}
Response (201 Created):
{    "message": "Order created         successfully",    "data": {        "id":             "d73a839a-8972-4252-907e-d8c            44ad0b6e3",        "item": "RAM",        "quantity": 3,        "status": "pending",        "createdBy":             "yash_admin@example.com"    }}

3. 
Delete order
Method: DELETE
Endpoint: /orders/{id}
Description: Deletes an order by its unique ID.
Path Variable: id — The UUID of the order to delete (e.g., d73a839a-8972-4252-907e-d8c44ad0b6e3)
